South African Police Commissioners’ Homes Burgled This Weekend, SAPA Says

-- B y   C a r l i   L o u r e n s
-- 
2011-06-26T07:42:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-26/south-african-police-commissioners-homes-burgled-this-weekend-sapa-says.html
Former South African Police
Commissioner  Jackie Selebi ’s house in Pretoria and Gauteng
province Police Commissioner Mzwandile Petros’s Johannesburg
home were burgled this weekend, South Africa Press Association
reported, citing a police spokesman.  The incidents weren’t related, Lieutenant Colonel
Tshisikhawe Ndou said, according to the Johannesburg-based  news
agency . The burglars took items including televisions from both
houses, according to the report.  Burglars lifted a gate off its railing to gain entry to
Selebi’s house and broke down the front door of Petros’s home,
SAPA said. Petros’s wife and children were at home when the
incident happened, though they weren’t hurt, the news agency
reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carli Lourens in Johannesburg at 
